# UCAB - ER Diagram

## Overview

The ER (Entity Relationship) Diagram represents the database structure of the UCAB Cab Booking System. It defines the entities, attributes, and relationships between Users, Drivers, Vehicles, and Rides.

---

## Entities

### User
Stores customer information.

Attributes:
- UserID (Primary Key)
- Name
- Email
- Password
- Phone Number

### Ride
Stores ride booking information.

Attributes:
- RideID (Primary Key)
- UserID (Foreign Key)
- DriverID (Foreign Key)
- Pickup Location
- Drop Location
- Fare
- Status

### Driver
Stores driver information.

Attributes:
- DriverID (Primary Key)
- Name
- Phone Number
- License Number
- Availability Status

### Vehicle
Stores vehicle information.

Attributes:
- VehicleID (Primary Key)
- DriverID (Foreign Key)
- Vehicle Number
- Vehicle Type
- Capacity

---

## Relationships

### User → Ride
Relationship Type: One-to-Many (1:M)

Description:
- One user can book multiple rides.
- Each ride belongs to only one user.

### Ride → Driver
Relationship Type: Many-to-One (M:1)

Description:
- Multiple rides can be handled by one driver.
- Each ride is assigned to one driver.

### Driver → Vehicle
Relationship Type: One-to-One (1:1)

Description:
- One driver is assigned one vehicle.
- One vehicle belongs to one driver.

---

## ER Diagram

```text
USER
 |
 | 1
 |------< Books >------ M
 |
RIDE
 |
 | M
 |------< Assigned To >------ 1
